  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Tax Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>Prepare Statutory Filings</p>\n<p>- Review tax computations and tax returns</p>\n<p>- Review other tax-related statutory e-filings</p>\n<p>- Research and analyse data to perform tax computations</p>\n<p>- Prepare accurate tax returns for e-filing</p>\n<p>- Identify developments that impact tax compliance</p>\n<p>- Keep proper tax-related documentation</p>\n<p>- Check notices of assessment</p>\n<p>- Review tax provisions</p>\n<p>Manage tax controversies</p>\n<p>- Review responses to manage tax controversies, including defending organisation’s or client’s tax positions and responding to tax authority’s queries</p>\n<p>- Research and analyse data to draft response to queries</p>\n<p>Identify tax risk areas</p>\n<p>- Gather information on tax, accounting, business, legal and governance issues to identify tax risks</p>\n<p>- Review implications of tax risks to the client or organisation</p>\n<p>- Monitor business operations and data periodically to ensure tax controls and other tax risk policies are adhered to</p>\n<p>Drafting of tax advice</p>\n<p>- Identify tax issues across different tax types to draw out implications to the client or management</p>\n<p>- Draft tax advice to the client or management</p>\n<p>- Ensure proper documentation of tax technical and/or tax legal positions supporting the tax advice</p>\n<p>Experience in handling Personal Tax</p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>- At least 4 years of experience with a professional accounting firm</p>\n<p>- Experience in dealing with tax advisory for Corporate Tax, Personal Tax and GST related matters a plus</p>\n<p>- Obtained / pursuing SIATP membership or equivalent</p>",
